code: @Override public Object[] extract(Tuple in) {     Object[] output.     if (order == null) {         // copy the whole tuple         output = new Object[in.getArity()].         for (int i = 0. i < in.getArity(). i++) {             output[i] = in.getField(i).         }     } else {         // copy user specified order         output = new Object[order.length].         for (int i = 0. i < order.length. i++) {             output[i] = in.getField(order[i]).         }     }     return output. }
